# Copy to release.env (git-ignored). Holds signing / publishing credentials.
#
# Releasing is done by GoReleaser in the Release workflow (.github/workflows/
# release.yml). In CI these values come from GitHub Actions *secrets*, not this
# file — see the "CI secrets" list below. This file lets you run a signed
# `goreleaser release` locally. When a value is absent, that step degrades to a
# no-op (unsigned / not published), so credential-less CI and PR builds succeed.
#
# CI secrets (Settings -> Secrets and variables -> Actions):
#   MACOS_SIGN_P12          base64 of the Developer ID Application .p12
#   MACOS_SIGN_PASSWORD     the .p12 export password
#   MACOS_NOTARY_KEY        base64 of the App Store Connect AuthKey .p8
#   MACOS_NOTARY_KEY_ID     the .p8 Key ID (e.g. G9W84MCW73)
#   MACOS_NOTARY_ISSUER_ID  App Store Connect Issuer ID (UUID) — enables notarization
#   HOMEBREW_TAP_TOKEN      PAT (contents:write) on jfigge/homebrew-tap

# ---- macOS code signing (GoReleaser / quill; runs on Linux) ----
# For a local signed build, export the base64 p12 + its password:
#   export MACOS_SIGN_P12="$(base64 < .keys/DeveloperID.p12 | tr -d '\n')"
# MACOS_SIGN_PASSWORD="<the .p12 export password>"

# ---- macOS notarization (App Store Connect API key; optional) ----
# AC_NOTARY_KEY_ID=G9W84MCW73
# AC_NOTARY_ISSUER_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
# AC_NOTARY_KEY_FILE=.keys/AuthKey_G9W84MCW73.p8

# ---- Windows Authenticode ----
# WINDOWS_CERT_FILE=/path/to/cert.pfx
# WINDOWS_CERT_PASSWORD=change-me
# WINDOWS_TIMESTAMP_URL=http://timestamp.digicert.com

# ---- Publishing ----
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxx           # GitHub Releases (provided by CI in Actions)
# HOMEBREW_TAP_TOKEN=ghp_xxx     # push cask to jfigge/homebrew-tap
